## 🧠 **Migration Plan: Local JSON → Hosted Database**

### 🎯 **Objective**
Migrate the task manager app from storing tasks in a local JSON file to a hosted database for better scalability, security, and collaboration.

---

## 📌 **1. Define Requirements**

| Feature | Current State | Target State |
|--------|---------------|--------------|
| Data Storage | Local JSON file | Hosted database (e.g., Firebase, Supabase, MongoDB) |
| Access | Local only | Remote access (web, mobile, etc.) |
| Security | No authentication | Optional authentication & data protection |
| Scalability | Limited | Easily scalable |
| Collaboration | Not supported | Real-time sync (optional) |

---

## 🛠️ **2. Choose a Hosted Database**

| Option | Pros | Cons |
|-------|------|------|
| **Firebase** | Easy setup, real-time sync, built-in auth | Free tier limited, less control |
| **Supabase** | Open source, PostgreSQL-based, easy to use | Slightly more complex setup |
| **MongoDB Atlas** | Flexible schema, powerful query system | More complex for small apps |
| **AWS DynamoDB / RDS** | Enterprise-grade, scalable | Steeper learning curve |

> **Recommended for small apps:** **Firebase** or **Supabase**

---

